					<item>
				<guid>http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/forum/t-14574559#post-5310401</guid>
				<title>Re: Corrections</title>
				<link>http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/forum/t-14574559/corrections#post-5310401</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 11 May 2022 23:41:22 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Ibissal</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>8033373</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>On the Barbarian: Path of the Ancestral Guardian page, the Spirit Shield ability only applies to <em>other</em> creatures, and should read <em>&quot;If you are raging and <strong>another creature</strong> you can see within 30 feet of you takes damage&#8230;&quot;</em> instead of <em>&quot;If you are raging and <strong>a creature</strong> you can see within 30 feet of you takes damage&#8230;&quot;</em></p> <p>Also, two minor inconsistencies with the Ancestral Protectors ability's text compared to the book:<br /> It has slightly different text in last sentence <em>&quot;that creature has resistance to the <strong>damage of the target’s attacks</strong>&quot;</em>, vs the book's <em>&quot;that creature has resistance to the <strong>damage dealt by the attack</strong>&quot;</em><br /> The ability is also missing the final sentence of <em>&quot;The effect on the target ends early if your rage ends.&quot;</em> (it is redundant, since the ability already states <em>&quot;While you're raging&quot;</em>, but I imagine it should be consistent with the book anyway)</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
